sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Kueue Controller<br/>(Job Reconciler)
    participant Cache as In-Memory Cache<br/>(Queue + ClusterQueue)
    participant Scheduler as Kueue Scheduler<br/>(Scheduling Loop)
    participant RemoteAPI as Remote Cluster API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Autoscaler as Cluster Autoscaler

    Note over User,Scheduler: Flow 1: Job Admission

    User->>K8sAPI: Submit Job (e.g., PyTorchJob)<br/>Auth: User credentials
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutating webhook call<br/>9443/TCP TLS (internal certs)<br/>Auth: API server webhook auth
    Webhook->>Webhook: Default queue label,<br/>suspend job, set managedBy
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Job
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validating webhook call<br/>9443/TCP TLS
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate queue-name,<br/>TAS annotations, constraints
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission allowed

    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event: Job created
    Controller->>Controller: Create Workload CR<br/>with PodSets & resource reqs
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Workload<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    K8sAPI-->>Cache: Watch event: Workload created
    Cache->>Cache: Update queue snapshot

    Scheduler->>Cache: Take snapshot of<br/>pending workloads
    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Evaluate against ClusterQueue<br/>quotas, priorities, fair sharing
    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Assign ResourceFlavors,<br/>check borrowing limits
    alt Preemption needed
        Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Evict lower-priority workloads<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    end
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Admit Workload<br/>(set admission status)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event: Workload admitted
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Unsuspend Job<br/>(set suspend=false)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job pods scheduled & running

    Note over User,Autoscaler: Flow 2: Provisioning Request Integration

    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Workload needs nodes<br/>not yet available
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Create ProvisioningRequest CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Autoscaler: Watch: ProvisioningRequest created
    Autoscaler->>Autoscaler: Provision nodes via<br/>cloud provider API (443/TCP)
    Autoscaler->>K8sAPI: Update ProvisioningRequest status<br/>Auth: Autoscaler SA
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch: PR status updated
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update AdmissionCheck → Ready<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Admit Workload

    Note over Controller,RemoteAPI: Flow 3: MultiKueue Federation (disabled in RHOAI)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Read MultiKueue kubeconfig Secret<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>RemoteAPI: Create remote Workload<br/>Auth: Kubeconfig credentials
    RemoteAPI-->>Controller: Remote Workload admitted
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Sync status to local Workload<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
